Kusmus High-Level Architecture (With Proprietary Definitions & Tech Stack)

![Kusmus AI Architecture](docs/images/kusmus_architecture.png)

---

1️⃣ Application Layer (UI / Client)

Purpose: Entry point for users to launch, manage, and monitor AI agents and pods.

Components:

Kusmus App / kusbot UI

Launch pods (your proprietary AI training and execution environments)

Monitor agent behavior and RL progress

Manage datasets and fine-tuning tasks

Display metrics, logs, and action history

Device Integrations

Access local files, apps, sensors through Iron Claw

Tech Stack:

Flutter / React Native / Kotlin / Swift for mobile

Electron / Tauri / Rust + Webview for desktop

React / Vue / Svelte for web

Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui for UI components

Redux / Zustand / React Query for state management

---

2️⃣ Pod Management & Orchestration Layer (Control Plane)

Purpose: Deploy, schedule, and manage your proprietary “pods”.

Your Pod Definition:

> A pod in Kusmus is a self-contained AI environment that includes:

Base model (LLM or agent)

Fine-tuning configuration

RL training scripts

Dataset connectors

Evaluation metrics

Different from general “pods” in Kubernetes, your pods are AI training + execution units, not just containers.

Components:

Pod Manager

Tracks versions & dependencies of pods

Handles updates, rollback, and composability

Job Scheduler

Allocates compute resources dynamically

Manages RL episodes and fine-tuning tasks

Model Registry

Stores fine-tuned model weights

Keeps pod metadata, version history, and reproducibility info

Metrics & Logging

Tracks RL rewards, agent actions, and pod performance

Tech Stack:

Kubernetes / Nomad / Custom Rust orchestrator

FastAPI / Node.js / Rust Actix backend

PostgreSQL / MySQL for pod registry & metadata

Prometheus + Grafana for metrics

RabbitMQ / Kafka / NATS for inter-service messaging

---

3️⃣ Pod Runtime Layer (Data Plane)

Purpose: Execute your pods, training loops, and RL workflows.

Components:

Pods (Kusmus definition)

Contain fine-tunable AI models

Include training scripts, RL loops, and dataset connectors

Versioned and composable — can reference other pods as modules

Training & RL Execution

Fine-tune models locally or on cloud GPUs

Execute RL feedback loops for agentic learning

Inter-Pod Communication

Share datasets or intermediate results between pods

Tech Stack:

Docker / Podman / WasmEdge for portable pods

PyTorch, TensorFlow, Hugging Face Transformers for AI

RLlib, Stable Baselines3, or OpenAI Gym for RL

Pandas, Arrow, SQLite / DuckDB for datasets

ONNX / PyTorch .pt / TensorFlow SavedModel for model serialization

---

4️⃣ Secure Agent Execution Layer (Iron Claw)

Purpose: Enable your models to act as fully autonomous agents safely.

Your Iron Claw Definition:

> Iron Claw is a security and execution engine that:

Wraps AI agents in a sandboxed environment

Grants controlled access to system apps (email, WhatsApp, local files)

Protects credentials and prevents data exfiltration

Logs agent actions for reinforcement learning feedback

Components:

WASM Sandboxing

Each agentic tool executes in isolated containers

Credential Vault

Secrets injected only to allowed actions

Allowlisted App Access

Network requests, apps, and device actions are controlled

RL Feedback Integration

Logs actions for training pods

Tech Stack:

Rust-based runtime

Wasmtime / Wasmer for sandboxing

HashiCorp Vault or custom encrypted secret store

Policy enforcement engine for capabilities

Proxy or allowlist for network requests

---

5️⃣ Compute Layer (Execution Infrastructure)

Purpose: Actual CPU/GPU resources for training, RL, and inference.

Components:

Local device GPU/CPU

Enterprise clusters / private GPU nodes

Cloud GPU providers (Google Cloud, AWS, Azure)

Distributed training via PyTorch Distributed, DeepSpeed, Ray

---

6️⃣ Data & Storage Layer

Purpose: Store datasets, RL logs, model weights, and pod states.

Components:

Persistent storage

S3 / MinIO / Google Cloud Storage / Azure Blob Storage

Database

PostgreSQL / MongoDB / Redis for caching

RL Feedback & Logs

Loki / ELK / Prometheus

Sandboxed local FS

OverlayFS or WASM virtual FS

---

7️⃣ High-Level Workflow (With Your Terms)

User App / kusbot UI
   ↓
Pod Manager / Control Plane
   ↓
Pod Runtime (your proprietary pods)
   ↓
Iron Claw (agentic execution)
   ↓
Compute Layer (Local/Cloud/Enterprise GPU)
   ↓
Data Layer (Datasets, RL logs, Model Weights)

Key Notes:

Pods = self-contained AI training + execution environments

Iron Claw = agentic runtime + security layer

kusbot = orchestrator + agent runtime

Users can fine-tune models, run RL agents, and execute tasks on real apps safely

---

8️⃣ Strategic Advantages

True agentic AI — can read emails, WhatsApp, and act on device

Secure & auditable — credentials, data, and actions controlled by Iron Claw

Composable & versioned pods — reusable AI environments for enterprise or personal use

Hybrid compute — pods run anywhere (local/cloud/enterprise)

Scalable RL & fine-tuning workflows — continuous improvement possible

